  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of life-saving health and GBV-related services to conflict-affected populations in Tanganyika province</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project provides immediate and life-saving health and GBV-related services to conflict-affected populations, especially women and children. The IRC supports 4 health facilities to implement the minimum primary health care (PHC) package, with a particular focus on reproductive, maternal and child health The IRC also engages with local women&#x2019;s community-based organizations (CBOs) and health facilities to ensure that women and girl survivors of GBV have access to appropriate services, benefit from a protective environment and have opportunities for social and economic reintegration.</narrative>
  </description>
